Recipe Suggestion Generator
The Recipe Suggestion Generator is a Streamlit app designed to inspire culinary creativity. It leverages Cohere's powerful language model to generate unique recipe suggestions based on a chosen cuisine type. Additionally, it proposes catchy names for each suggested recipe, adding a fun and personalized touch.

Features
Cuisine-Based Recipe Generation: Input a cuisine type to receive tailored recipe suggestions.
Creative Recipe Names: Each recipe comes with a suggested catchy name.
Adjustable Creativity Level: Control the creativity of the suggestions with an adjustable slider.

Installation
Clone the Repository

bash
Copy code
git clone [repository-url]
cd [repository-folder]
Set Up a Virtual Environment (Optional but recommended)

bash
Copy code
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows use `venv\Scripts\activate`
Install Dependencies

bash
Copy code
pip install -r requirements.txt
Environment Variables

You will need a Cohere API key to use this app.
Set up the API key as an environment variable CO_KEY.
Usage
Run the Streamlit App

bash
Copy code
streamlit run app.py
Using the App

Enter a cuisine type in the input field.
Adjust the number of recipes and the level of creativity as desired.
Click on "Generate Recipe" to receive your recipe suggestions and their names.
Contributing
Contributions to the Recipe Suggestion Generator are welcome. Please read CONTRIBUTING.md for guidelines on how to contribute to this project.



